                <head>43. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In a memorandum to the President dated November 10, Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName> recommended that, in view of the
                    positive development of U.S. relations with Romania and Bulgaria in recent
                    months, the Legations at Bucharest and Sofia be raised to Embassy status at an
                    early date. The President rejected the suggestion. See Part 1, <ref
                        target="#d34">Document 34</ref>.</p>
            </div>
